OL,3,CAdmin worker unfairly sacked after
OL,4,Caccidentally abusing client, tribunal
OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FShe was sacked for gross misconduct in
OL,8,FJune 2023, a week after she had sent
OL,9,Fthe message to the customer instead of
OL,10,Fthe company's installations manager
OL,11,FKarl Gibbons, an employment tribunal
OL,12,Fin Reading heard.
OL,14,FMs Jones was awarded #5,484.74 after
OL,15,Fthe tribunal ruled she had been
OL,16,Funfairly dismissed.
OL,18,FThe customer had made "repeated
OL,19,Fcomplaints" about his order and had
OL,20,Ftried to get a full refund of the cost
OL,21,Fof his curtains.
