OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FMs Jones was "shocked and upset" as
OL,8,Fshe realised her mistake, put the
OL,9,Fcaller on speaker so a colleague could
OL,10,Fhear and apologised "profusely" but
OL,11,Fthe customer's wife wanted to speak to
OL,12,Fthe manager Jacqueline Smith.
OL,14,FIn a later telephone call, Mrs Smith
OL,15,Fapologised for what Ms Jones had done
OL,16,Fand said she would be reprimanded.
OL,18,FThe customer's wife asked how she was
OL,19,Fgoing to be compensated and was told
OL,20,Fshe could not get the curtains for
OL,21,Ffree.
