OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FBut the tribunal heard that neither Ms
OL,8,FJones nor the customer was
OL,9,Finterviewed, no notes were produced by
OL,10,FMrs Smith and no written account of
OL,11,Fthe decision was made.
OL,13,FThe customer had contacted the company
OL,14,Fdirectly and made further threats
OL,15,Fabout publicising the incident, in
OL,16,Fparticular by leaving a poor review on
OL,17,FTrustpilot and bosses decided to "get
OL,18,Frid of" Ms Jones.
