OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FWhen she arrived at work, Mrs Smith,
OL,8,Fwho was crying, handed her an
OL,9,Finvitation to a disciplinary meeting.
OL,11,FA letter was later sent to the
OL,12,Fcustomer's wife informing her that Ms
OL,13,FJones had been dismissed "following
OL,14,Fthe disgraceful email that was sent to
OL,15,Fyour husband in error".
OL,17,FMs Jones lodged an appeal against her
OL,18,Fdismissal on 14 grounds, but it was
OL,19,Fdenied.
