OL,5,Crules
OL,7,F"It is clear that on the day of the
OL,8,Fincident, Mrs Smith thought that the
OL,9,Fclaimant's mistake was regrettable but
OL,10,Fnot a disciplinary matter."
OL,12,FThe judge said: "The disciplinary
OL,13,Fprocess and the dismissal were a sham
OL,14,Fdesigned to placate the customer.
OL,16,F"This is clear from the fact that Mrs
OL,17,FSmith immediately informed the
OL,18,Fcustomer that (Ms Jones) had been
OL,19,Fdismissed (notably, without any
OL,20,Fapparent regard for the Claimant's
OL,21,Fdata protection rights)."
